Importance measures, such as attention, are frequently used to explain which words
are important. But is the explanation true to the model?
Measuring the truthfulness of an explanation is called faithfulness. This is non-trivial
because the true explanation is unknown. Therefore different works use proxy-
measures to determine faithfulness. These works have important limitations, which
In this work, we introduce the proxy-measure Recursive ROAR, an improvement on
ROAR, which can determine if an explanation is either faithful or non-faithful.
